  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the Life Quality of Poor Farmers in Dong Thap Province through VBHCD</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of this project is to improve the quality of life for poor farm households in two districts of Dong Thap Province in the Mekong Delta of Vietnam.  A total 448 families will be divided into 20 self-help groups. The groups will be trained in Heifer Cornerstones, the Participatory Self-review Planning method and the Values-based Holistic Community Development model. The project will provide 224 heifers to the 224 original families in Cao Lanh District and Thap Muoi District. These families will also receive microcredit funds of $150 per family to initiate income-generating activities, such as fish-raising and growing cash crops. In three years, the project will help increase the income of the participants, who will pass on the gift. In addition to animal distribution, all participants will receive both technical and non-technical trainings on livestock management, crop production, sustainable agriculture skills, enterprise development, natural resource management and others. The project will also  provide trainings special topics for youth. These youth will be the bridge for the project to reach other youth within and outside the project communities. The Dong Thap Provincial Government will contribute 50% of the funds for this project to Heifer Viet Nam.</narrative>
  </description>
